WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:10.552 --> 00:00:13.847 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA] I'll take a look ahead.
You wait over there.

00:00:13.930 --> 00:00:15.140 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Got it.

00:00:16.391 --> 00:00:18.309 position:50% align:center
Yuito.

00:00:18.393 --> 00:00:19.978 position:50% align:center
You guys. Hey.

00:00:20.061 --> 00:00:22.814 position:50% align:center
How are you?
Feel any better?

00:00:22.897 --> 00:00:26.609 position:50% align:center
Well, my memory's intact
for now, least I think so.

00:00:26.693 --> 00:00:29.237 position:50% align:center
And if we need it, I have this.

00:00:29.320 --> 00:00:30.780 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:00:30.864 --> 00:00:33.783 position:50% align:center
That looks... scary.

00:00:33.867 --> 00:00:37.912 position:50% align:center
Yeah. It was prescribed
by the hospital, but...

00:00:41.332 --> 00:00:43.418 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
I found them in the old subway.

00:00:43.501 --> 00:00:46.004 position:50% align:center
Is it some kind of drug?

00:00:46.087 --> 00:00:48.548 position:50% align:center
Unless your condition
gets really dire,

00:00:48.631 --> 00:00:51.217 position:50% align:center
I don't think you
should take that.

00:00:51.301 --> 00:00:53.261 position:50% align:center
Okay, I won't.

00:00:54.387 --> 00:00:56.556 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA] It should be
around here somewhere.

00:00:56.639 --> 00:00:59.726 position:50% align:center
Right after those OSF
deserters ran away to Seiran,

00:00:59.809 --> 00:01:01.561 position:50% align:center
this is where they were spotted.

00:01:03.104 --> 00:01:06.149 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI] I wonder what they
were doing in a place like this?

00:01:10.278 --> 00:01:12.572 position:50% align:center
--[static]
--[grunts]

00:01:16.910 --> 00:01:18.787 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:01:25.460 --> 00:01:30.465 position:50% align:center
♪

00:02:57.844 --> 00:03:01.389 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI gasps] There doesn't
seem to be anyone nearby.

00:03:02.932 --> 00:03:05.018 position:50% align:center
Then maybe the report
wasn't right.

00:03:05.101 --> 00:03:07.354 position:50% align:center
Could have been some bad intel.

00:03:07.437 --> 00:03:09.564 position:50% align:center
Let's look around some more.

00:03:09.647 --> 00:03:12.984 position:50% align:center
I mean, all we can do for now is
try and complete our assignment.

00:03:13.068 --> 00:03:16.905 position:50% align:center
True. Until we decide our
next move, that is.

00:03:18.907 --> 00:03:21.701 position:50% align:center
My intent is simply
to undo the wrongs

00:03:21.785 --> 00:03:23.453 position:50% align:center
of the New Himukan regime.

00:03:23.536 --> 00:03:24.913 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:03:24.996 --> 00:03:27.207 position:50% align:center
What do you mean by that?

00:03:27.290 --> 00:03:28.667 position:50% align:center
Karen and I...

00:03:28.750 --> 00:03:32.170 position:50% align:center
...we've actually found
a bit of common ground.

00:03:32.253 --> 00:03:36.299 position:50% align:center
My fiancée Alice looked into why
people were turning into Others.

00:03:36.383 --> 00:03:40.053 position:50% align:center
Once the personality rehab and
metamorphosis were found out,

00:03:40.136 --> 00:03:43.264 position:50% align:center
Karen and I vowed
to change things.

00:03:43.348 --> 00:03:47.644 position:50% align:center
After all, we were close enough
to the top brass to do so.

00:03:47.727 --> 00:03:51.981 position:50% align:center
But Karen isn't the type to
endear himself to his superiors.

00:03:52.065 --> 00:03:54.567 position:50% align:center
And that was why,
just as ordered,

00:03:54.651 --> 00:03:59.114 position:50% align:center
I took the responsibility
of mobilizing the OSF.

00:03:59.197 --> 00:04:01.282 position:50% align:center
But now that Karen's defected,

00:04:01.366 --> 00:04:04.828 position:50% align:center
there's no need to play the
role of the government pawn.

00:04:04.911 --> 00:04:06.538 position:50% align:center
I'll set things right.

00:04:06.621 --> 00:04:09.624 position:50% align:center
I know there's another way
of doing so besides his.

00:04:09.708 --> 00:04:11.501 position:50% align:center
Another way?

00:04:11.584 --> 00:04:14.879 position:50% align:center
Like how? Do you have
something planned?

00:04:14.963 --> 00:04:18.299 position:50% align:center
Well, the truth is,
New Himuka's been doing research

00:04:18.383 --> 00:04:21.511 position:50% align:center
by way of illegal
human experimentation.

00:04:21.594 --> 00:04:24.514 position:50% align:center
It's heinous and it needs
to be brought to the light.

00:04:24.597 --> 00:04:27.475 position:50% align:center
After all, if the public
finds out what the government

00:04:27.559 --> 00:04:30.020 position:50% align:center
is doing, they won't
stand for it.

00:04:30.103 --> 00:04:31.646 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Hm?

00:04:31.730 --> 00:04:33.815 position:50% align:center
Even if the truth does come out,

00:04:33.898 --> 00:04:37.110 position:50% align:center
the misdeeds of this government
won't simply be erased.

00:04:37.193 --> 00:04:40.780 position:50% align:center
But in doing so, we may
get the fire started.

00:04:40.864 --> 00:04:43.366 position:50% align:center
So, with Karen working
from the outside

00:04:43.450 --> 00:04:45.577 position:50% align:center
and you working from the inside,

00:04:45.660 --> 00:04:48.329 position:50% align:center
you're hoping that you
can bring about change.

00:04:48.413 --> 00:04:50.040 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Yes, that's the idea.

00:04:50.123 --> 00:04:52.375 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]
I think I can help!

00:04:52.459 --> 00:04:55.295 position:50% align:center
Please let me,
Major General Fubuki!

00:04:55.378 --> 00:04:59.090 position:50% align:center
If I just speak to my brother,
he might listen!

00:04:59.174 --> 00:05:00.425 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Hmph!

00:05:00.508 --> 00:05:03.219 position:50% align:center
Not sure it's wise to
involve Chief Sumeragi.

00:05:03.303 --> 00:05:06.514 position:50% align:center
He may be your brother,
but he's part of the government.

00:05:06.598 --> 00:05:08.058 position:50% align:center
It's a dangerous move.

00:05:08.141 --> 00:05:12.187 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I know! But I
can't just do nothing.

00:05:12.270 --> 00:05:13.438 position:50% align:center
Yuito...

00:05:13.521 --> 00:05:15.231 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI gasps]

00:05:15.315 --> 00:05:18.610 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Poor Naomi. And Nagi.

00:05:19.444 --> 00:05:21.905 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]

00:05:21.988 --> 00:05:23.990 position:50% align:center
Come on, Major General!

00:05:24.074 --> 00:05:26.534 position:50% align:center
I'm begging you!
Let us fix this!

00:05:26.618 --> 00:05:28.370 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Hm!

00:05:28.453 --> 00:05:31.664 position:50% align:center
Yuito, you're a commander.

00:05:31.748 --> 00:05:33.083 position:50% align:center
Digging into all
this doesn't just

00:05:33.166 --> 00:05:37.879 position:50% align:center
put you at risk but them,
too. Your entire platoon.

00:05:37.962 --> 00:05:39.255 position:50% align:center
Do you understand?

00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:42.634 position:50% align:center
'Course I do, so remove
me as a commander!

00:05:42.717 --> 00:05:44.260 position:50% align:center
That's not an option.

00:05:44.344 --> 00:05:47.389 position:50% align:center
So, what, then?

00:05:47.472 --> 00:05:48.973 position:50% align:center
That's fine.

00:05:49.057 --> 00:05:51.434 position:50% align:center
If he can't quit, that means the
rest of us will have to agree

00:05:51.518 --> 00:05:53.395 position:50% align:center
to be willing participants.

00:05:53.478 --> 00:05:55.271 position:50% align:center
You can count me in, for sure.

00:05:55.355 --> 00:05:56.523 position:50% align:center
Yeah, me too.

00:05:56.606 --> 00:05:58.400 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:05:58.483 --> 00:06:02.987 position:50% align:center
Naomi, she didn't deserve that.
And if the government was

00:06:03.071 --> 00:06:06.783 position:50% align:center
involved in what happened,
they should pay.

00:06:06.866 --> 00:06:09.119 position:50% align:center
Please allow me to
help out as well.

00:06:09.202 --> 00:06:12.288 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Thanks, guys.

00:06:12.372 --> 00:06:14.374 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Hm. Understood.

00:06:14.457 --> 00:06:17.419 position:50% align:center
If that's how you feel,
then I'll have you join in.

00:06:17.502 --> 00:06:19.254 position:50% align:center
Thank you, sir!

00:06:19.337 --> 00:06:22.382 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] However, I'll be
the one to make the plan.

00:06:22.465 --> 00:06:26.511 position:50% align:center
Just keep fulfilling your duties
until then. Are we clear?

00:06:31.850 --> 00:06:32.976 position:50% align:center
[KAITO]
I see.

00:06:33.059 --> 00:06:36.354 position:50% align:center
So it's a new security
protocol for Arahabaki.

00:06:36.438 --> 00:06:37.897 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] We couldn't
afford to risk a repeat

00:06:37.981 --> 00:06:40.442 position:50% align:center
of the Suoh Incident.

00:06:40.525 --> 00:06:45.530 position:50% align:center
If I may, I'll enter the secure
site and verify it myself.

00:06:45.613 --> 00:06:48.241 position:50% align:center
[KAITO]
Hm...

00:06:48.324 --> 00:06:51.411 position:50% align:center
All right.
Consider it done, then.

00:06:51.494 --> 00:06:54.956 position:50% align:center
I'll have Central Control
provide you with an entry pass.

00:06:55.040 --> 00:06:56.624 position:50% align:center
I appreciate it, sir.

00:06:59.919 --> 00:07:03.590 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI gasps] There!
Above us at twelve-o'-clock!

00:07:07.052 --> 00:07:08.303 position:50% align:center
Not what we came for,

00:07:08.386 --> 00:07:10.430 position:50% align:center
but we can take
care of it anyway!

00:07:10.513 --> 00:07:11.723 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:07:12.849 --> 00:07:14.184 position:50% align:center
[shouts]

00:07:16.144 --> 00:07:21.149 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:07:22.901 --> 00:07:24.527 position:50% align:center
Yuito!

00:07:24.611 --> 00:07:28.448 position:50% align:center
[WATARU] Uh-oh, that's not good.
Those are abnormal brainwaves.

00:07:28.531 --> 00:07:30.241 position:50% align:center
Don't use psionics!

00:07:30.325 --> 00:07:31.951 position:50% align:center
I'll help you!

00:07:32.035 --> 00:07:33.244 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:07:38.875 --> 00:07:41.086 position:50% align:center
[grunts, gasps]

00:07:43.963 --> 00:07:45.382 position:50% align:center
Are you alright?

00:07:45.465 --> 00:07:48.134 position:50% align:center
Sound... Sound is the messenger.
Dragonfly gap.

00:07:48.218 --> 00:07:49.511 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
Um, what?

00:07:49.594 --> 00:07:53.264 position:50% align:center
Azuma untamed. Lower partake?

00:07:53.348 --> 00:07:55.934 position:50% align:center
Hey, Yuito? What's wrong?

00:07:56.017 --> 00:07:58.561 position:50% align:center
[grunts]
I'm not making sense!

00:07:58.645 --> 00:08:00.814 position:50% align:center
Apple, home, return, apple!

00:08:00.897 --> 00:08:02.899 position:50% align:center
Have you been injured, Yuito?

00:08:02.982 --> 00:08:04.192 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]

00:08:05.902 --> 00:08:07.112 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:08:08.238 --> 00:08:10.323 position:50% align:center
[shouts]

00:08:11.700 --> 00:08:13.034 position:50% align:center
Get him out of here!

00:08:13.118 --> 00:08:16.246 position:50% align:center
[YUITO, HANABI grunting]

00:08:16.329 --> 00:08:18.331 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
Almost there.

00:08:18.415 --> 00:08:21.126 position:50% align:center
Wait here, okay?

00:08:21.209 --> 00:08:23.712 position:50% align:center
[YUITO] I feel like my
head might explode.

00:08:25.672 --> 00:08:27.090 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:08:29.843 --> 00:08:32.595 position:50% align:center
[pants]

00:08:35.849 --> 00:08:38.768 position:50% align:center
The Kunad Gate is beginning
to grow much faster now, sir.

00:08:38.852 --> 00:08:40.020 position:50% align:center
It's like...

00:08:40.103 --> 00:08:41.438 position:50% align:center
Like what?

00:08:41.521 --> 00:08:46.067 position:50% align:center
Well, sir, that it's responding
to some external force.

00:08:46.151 --> 00:08:47.694 position:50% align:center
[KAITO]
Hm...

00:08:52.115 --> 00:08:54.159 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Huh?

00:08:54.242 --> 00:08:55.744 position:50% align:center
Yuito?

00:08:57.996 --> 00:09:02.417 position:50% align:center
Any changes? No response
from Naomi yet?

00:09:02.500 --> 00:09:04.669 position:50% align:center
[KASANE sighs]

00:09:04.753 --> 00:09:06.046 position:50% align:center
Geez.

00:09:10.842 --> 00:09:14.679 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI growls]

00:09:14.763 --> 00:09:17.474 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI] What are these
ampules you're giving Naomi?

00:09:18.892 --> 00:09:20.518 position:50% align:center
[inaudible]

00:09:21.811 --> 00:09:24.564 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:09:24.647 --> 00:09:25.899 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Damn it!

00:09:28.276 --> 00:09:31.321 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]
No! My psionics don't work!

00:09:31.404 --> 00:09:32.864 position:50% align:center
[growls]

00:09:32.947 --> 00:09:34.699 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:09:34.783 --> 00:09:35.575 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA]
Yuito!

00:09:35.658 --> 00:09:36.868 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps] 

00:09:40.330 --> 00:09:42.123 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
This is my only choice!

00:09:46.503 --> 00:09:47.837 position:50% align:center
[YUITO coughs]

00:09:47.921 --> 00:09:49.673 position:50% align:center
Tsugumi!

00:09:49.756 --> 00:09:50.799 position:50% align:center
I'll take a look.

00:09:50.882 --> 00:09:52.342 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:09:52.425 --> 00:09:55.011 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI] The abnormal
brainwaves are starting to fade!

00:09:56.930 --> 00:09:58.098 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]
Oh wow.

00:09:58.181 --> 00:09:59.557 position:50% align:center
You okay?

00:09:59.641 --> 00:10:00.850 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:10:05.855 --> 00:10:08.900 position:50% align:center
[YUITO yells]

00:10:24.541 --> 00:10:25.834 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI, LUKA gasp]

00:10:28.753 --> 00:10:31.715 position:50% align:center
[WATARU] No anomalies
in any of your stats.

00:10:31.798 --> 00:10:33.717 position:50% align:center
So how do you feel? All good?

00:10:33.800 --> 00:10:36.219 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Yeah, I think I'm fine.

00:10:36.302 --> 00:10:37.971 position:50% align:center
What a relief!

00:10:38.054 --> 00:10:40.807 position:50% align:center
Honestly, that drug helped.

00:10:40.890 --> 00:10:43.977 position:50% align:center
If I hadn't taken that stuff,
I'd have been done for.

00:10:44.060 --> 00:10:45.687 position:50% align:center
That's good to know.

00:10:45.770 --> 00:10:47.939 position:50% align:center
Now that one of us has tried it,

00:10:48.023 --> 00:10:50.316 position:50% align:center
you think it's okay
to assume it's safe?

00:10:50.400 --> 00:10:54.237 position:50% align:center
[YUITO] I mean, it smelled funny
and it tasted gross, but...

00:10:54.320 --> 00:10:58.241 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Wait. There's
something over there.

00:10:58.324 --> 00:11:01.369 position:50% align:center
Wataru, are you able
to get a reading?

00:11:01.453 --> 00:11:05.040 position:50% align:center
The Extinction Belt's too dense
right now, so I can't see much.

00:11:05.123 --> 00:11:07.876 position:50% align:center
What else can you guys tell me?

00:11:07.959 --> 00:11:10.253 position:50% align:center
I see trucks.

00:11:10.337 --> 00:11:12.005 position:50% align:center
There are two of them.

00:11:12.088 --> 00:11:14.591 position:50% align:center
And it looks like they're
headed toward Seiran.

00:11:17.761 --> 00:11:19.012 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:11:19.095 --> 00:11:20.472 position:50% align:center
What is it?

00:11:20.555 --> 00:11:23.975 position:50% align:center
Um, it's nothing. I thought
I saw something, but, no--

00:11:24.059 --> 00:11:25.602 position:50% align:center
[WATARU]
Target sighted!

00:11:25.685 --> 00:11:27.354 position:50% align:center
They're transport trucks
registered to the

00:11:27.437 --> 00:11:31.274 position:50% align:center
Seiran Regional Force.
They came from Togetsu.

00:11:31.358 --> 00:11:32.859 position:50% align:center
What's that?

00:11:32.942 --> 00:11:35.278 position:50% align:center
I'm pretty sure that's the city
where the moon worshippers live.

00:11:35.362 --> 00:11:39.741 position:50% align:center
Yeah. It's a theocratic
autonomous region.

00:11:39.824 --> 00:11:41.159 position:50% align:center
Kagero...

00:11:41.242 --> 00:11:45.038 position:50% align:center
Oh, right! That's where
Kagero comes from, too.

00:11:45.121 --> 00:11:46.456 position:50% align:center
Well, in any case,

00:11:46.539 --> 00:11:49.292 position:50% align:center
it looks like we have a
clear trail to follow now.

00:12:03.640 --> 00:12:05.225 position:50% align:center
[YUITO, TSUMUGI gasp]

00:12:06.351 --> 00:12:07.769 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
The trucks.

00:12:07.852 --> 00:12:09.062 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI]
Yeah.

00:12:09.145 --> 00:12:10.939 position:50% align:center
Let me get a closer look.

00:12:15.443 --> 00:12:16.361 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Hm.

00:12:16.444 --> 00:12:17.946 position:50% align:center
[WATARU]
I did some digging.

00:12:18.029 --> 00:12:20.615 position:50% align:center
But there's no info
about that facility.

00:12:20.699 --> 00:12:22.325 position:50% align:center
I wonder what it could be?

00:12:22.409 --> 00:12:24.661 position:50% align:center
Why is it out here in
the middle of nowhere?

00:12:24.744 --> 00:12:27.580 position:50% align:center
Do you guys think it
belongs to Seiran?

00:12:27.664 --> 00:12:29.833 position:50% align:center
I've got a bad feeling.

00:12:29.916 --> 00:12:32.877 position:50% align:center
Wait up. Luka found
something suspicious.

00:12:32.961 --> 00:12:34.587 position:50% align:center
--[YUITO] Yeah?
--[HANABI] What is it?

00:12:38.049 --> 00:12:39.676 position:50% align:center
I managed to grab
some of the cargo

00:12:39.759 --> 00:12:41.469 position:50% align:center
that those trucks were carrying.

00:12:44.931 --> 00:12:46.224 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:12:53.773 --> 00:12:55.233 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
No way...

00:12:55.316 --> 00:12:57.068 position:50% align:center
And what make it worse...

00:12:57.152 --> 00:13:00.238 position:50% align:center
Every one of those trucks
is packed full of them.

00:13:00.321 --> 00:13:02.490 position:50% align:center
So, my eyes
didn't deceive me.

00:13:02.574 --> 00:13:04.284 position:50% align:center
What's happening here?

00:13:09.080 --> 00:13:10.665 position:50% align:center
Okay, let's move.

00:13:10.749 --> 00:13:11.958 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI]
Mm!

00:13:15.003 --> 00:13:17.756 position:50% align:center
Uh? Hey! You can't--!

00:13:17.839 --> 00:13:19.049 position:50% align:center
[RESEARCHER A groans]

00:13:21.301 --> 00:13:23.386 position:50% align:center
[HANABI, YUITO gasp]

00:13:23.470 --> 00:13:25.138 position:50% align:center
[LUKA]
Anything?

00:13:25.221 --> 00:13:26.639 position:50% align:center
Yeah, a key.

00:13:36.066 --> 00:13:37.442 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
What is this?

00:13:38.777 --> 00:13:41.071 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
A production line, maybe?

00:13:41.154 --> 00:13:42.364 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI gasps]

00:13:44.491 --> 00:13:46.993 position:50% align:center
Probably the same
contents as the others.

00:13:48.119 --> 00:13:49.454 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI]
Mm.

00:13:49.537 --> 00:13:52.499 position:50% align:center
You mean... those are?

00:13:52.582 --> 00:13:54.834 position:50% align:center
They're all filled
with human brains.

00:13:54.918 --> 00:13:58.046 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]
What the hell is this place?

00:13:58.129 --> 00:14:02.342 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA] Are they...
manufacturing brains?

00:14:02.425 --> 00:14:06.096 position:50% align:center
It's so horrifying.
What could they be used for?

00:14:06.179 --> 00:14:10.225 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
What's that smell? It's strong.

00:14:10.308 --> 00:14:14.104 position:50% align:center
You're right. It smells
like blood, don't you think?

00:14:14.187 --> 00:14:16.439 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Oh no...

00:14:26.741 --> 00:14:27.951 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:14:29.744 --> 00:14:31.538 position:50% align:center
[grunts, coughs]

00:14:31.621 --> 00:14:34.666 position:50% align:center
Right. These ampules.
They hold the drugs

00:14:34.749 --> 00:14:36.918 position:50% align:center
mass-produced by
Spring Pharmaceuticals.

00:14:37.002 --> 00:14:39.379 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
Take it easy.

00:14:39.462 --> 00:14:40.839 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
It can't be...

00:14:40.922 --> 00:14:46.219 position:50% align:center
[alarm buzzes]

00:14:46.302 --> 00:14:48.430 position:50% align:center
Yuito's platoon is here?

00:14:48.513 --> 00:14:51.599 position:50% align:center
Seems that way. What now?

00:14:51.683 --> 00:14:52.892 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:14:56.521 --> 00:14:58.940 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO]
Hey, did you hear me, or what?

00:15:01.943 --> 00:15:03.945 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Yuito's group is onto us.

00:15:06.448 --> 00:15:09.284 position:50% align:center
[KASANE] If this facility
is exposed for what it is,

00:15:09.367 --> 00:15:11.578 position:50% align:center
I can't take care of Naomi.

00:15:16.624 --> 00:15:18.251 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA]
Damn!

00:15:18.335 --> 00:15:19.336 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Yuito!

00:15:19.419 --> 00:15:22.589 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]
Kasane!

00:15:22.672 --> 00:15:24.090 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI, HANABI gasp]

00:15:24.174 --> 00:15:28.261 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry for all this, Tsugumi.
It isn't what I wanted.

00:15:28.345 --> 00:15:30.221 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI sighs]

00:15:30.305 --> 00:15:33.099 position:50% align:center
Okay. Tell me what's
going on, right now!

00:15:33.183 --> 00:15:34.476 position:50% align:center
[KASANE grunts]

00:15:34.559 --> 00:15:37.270 position:50% align:center
Is it really that hard of
a concept to figure out?

00:15:37.354 --> 00:15:39.105 position:50% align:center
This building is the
Seiran-based plant

00:15:39.189 --> 00:15:40.899 position:50% align:center
for Spring Pharmaceuticals.

00:15:40.982 --> 00:15:42.400 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]

00:15:42.484 --> 00:15:44.944 position:50% align:center
Actually, that's not quite it.
My family runs this place

00:15:45.028 --> 00:15:46.696 position:50% align:center
jointly with the
Nation of Seiran.

00:15:46.780 --> 00:15:49.491 position:50% align:center
It's used for Others research.

00:15:49.574 --> 00:15:53.078 position:50% align:center
Kasane... Do you know what
kinds of things they do here?

00:15:53.161 --> 00:15:55.705 position:50% align:center
Please say no.

00:15:55.789 --> 00:15:57.540 position:50% align:center
Of course, I do.

00:15:57.624 --> 00:16:00.502 position:50% align:center
These ampules
you're giving Naomi.

00:16:00.585 --> 00:16:02.545 position:50% align:center
I want you to tell me
what's in them.

00:16:04.172 --> 00:16:05.965 position:50% align:center
Drugs made from human brains.

00:16:06.049 --> 00:16:08.093 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:16:08.176 --> 00:16:10.345 position:50% align:center
No way, really?

00:16:10.428 --> 00:16:13.098 position:50% align:center
You gave my sister
human brains?

00:16:13.181 --> 00:16:14.432 position:50% align:center
Inside this facility,

00:16:14.516 --> 00:16:16.810 position:50% align:center
we're doing research
on an Other Weapon.

00:16:16.893 --> 00:16:20.021 position:50% align:center
We need it for the final
battle with New Himuka.

00:16:20.105 --> 00:16:22.190 position:50% align:center
An Other Weapon?

00:16:22.273 --> 00:16:25.819 position:50% align:center
[KAREN] We planned to transplant
a human brain into an Other,

00:16:25.902 --> 00:16:27.946 position:50% align:center
and then we'd have a
psionic user's brain

00:16:28.029 --> 00:16:31.574 position:50% align:center
control it by using SAS.

00:16:31.658 --> 00:16:34.035 position:50% align:center
Unfortunately, they began
deploying Others

00:16:34.119 --> 00:16:37.205 position:50% align:center
that were derived from
more compatible humans,

00:16:37.288 --> 00:16:40.375 position:50% align:center
which required the
drug in these ampules.

00:16:40.458 --> 00:16:43.378 position:50% align:center
It stabilizes the brain
and quite effectively.

00:16:43.461 --> 00:16:46.089 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps] If you're
trying to use my sister

00:16:46.172 --> 00:16:47.549 position:50% align:center
as some kind of weapon--

00:16:47.632 --> 00:16:51.386 position:50% align:center
That's nothing but a means
of placating Seiran for now.

00:16:51.469 --> 00:16:54.723 position:50% align:center
The true intention of
this facility is to change

00:16:54.806 --> 00:16:58.518 position:50% align:center
human-derived Others
back to their natural forms.

00:16:58.601 --> 00:17:01.813 position:50% align:center
Listen, Kasane! Whatever you're
up to, it ends right here!

00:17:01.896 --> 00:17:03.106 position:50% align:center
[KASANE grunts]

00:17:04.107 --> 00:17:05.900 position:50% align:center
There is no other option.

00:17:05.984 --> 00:17:07.610 position:50% align:center
Now, take my life!

00:17:07.694 --> 00:17:10.280 position:50% align:center
Do it for the sake
of this world!

00:17:10.363 --> 00:17:12.991 position:50% align:center
If you're really a part
of all this insanity,

00:17:13.074 --> 00:17:15.160 position:50% align:center
that means you <i>did</i>
kill my father.

00:17:15.243 --> 00:17:16.453 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:17:18.830 --> 00:17:23.835 position:50% align:center
[YUITO, KASANE grunting]

00:17:25.128 --> 00:17:26.671 position:50% align:center
[shouts]

00:17:26.755 --> 00:17:27.964 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA grunts]

00:17:29.507 --> 00:17:30.467 position:50% align:center
Come on!

00:17:30.550 --> 00:17:31.760 position:50% align:center
[shouts]

00:17:39.434 --> 00:17:41.186 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, YUITO grunt]

00:17:47.108 --> 00:17:51.029 position:50% align:center
Kasane, are you actually
trying to kill Yuito?

00:17:51.112 --> 00:17:53.114 position:50% align:center
It isn't just New Himuka!

00:17:53.198 --> 00:17:55.575 position:50% align:center
Seiran's every bit
as evil as they are!

00:17:55.658 --> 00:17:57.577 position:50% align:center
That drug that they're
mass-producing,

00:17:57.660 --> 00:17:59.162 position:50% align:center
it's made out of human brains!

00:17:59.245 --> 00:18:04.417 position:50% align:center
I know that. But without those
ampules, my sister will die.

00:18:04.501 --> 00:18:06.044 position:50% align:center
Are you saying?

00:18:06.127 --> 00:18:09.130 position:50% align:center
We get it. It does
sound unthinkable.

00:18:09.214 --> 00:18:10.548 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:18:10.632 --> 00:18:13.677 position:50% align:center
But then, if it's to protect
someone they love,

00:18:13.760 --> 00:18:15.929 position:50% align:center
people will sometimes
do the unthinkable.

00:18:16.012 --> 00:18:17.555 position:50% align:center
[YUITO, LUKA gasp]

00:18:17.639 --> 00:18:20.767 position:50% align:center
I will protect her,
no matter what!

00:18:22.519 --> 00:18:25.355 position:50% align:center
[KASANE grunts]

00:18:25.438 --> 00:18:26.648 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:18:29.275 --> 00:18:30.819 position:50% align:center
[groans]

00:18:30.902 --> 00:18:32.112 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]

00:18:34.406 --> 00:18:35.615 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI grunts]

00:18:37.409 --> 00:18:39.411 position:50% align:center
Luka, let's get
out of here! Now!

00:18:39.494 --> 00:18:41.079 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:18:41.162 --> 00:18:43.039 position:50% align:center
How could you let them escape?

00:18:43.123 --> 00:18:45.834 position:50% align:center
What if people find
out about this place?

00:18:45.917 --> 00:18:47.711 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI sighs]

00:18:47.794 --> 00:18:50.880 position:50% align:center
Kasane. Now that we know what
the drug is made out of,

00:18:50.964 --> 00:18:52.340 position:50% align:center
what do you want
us to do about it?

00:18:52.424 --> 00:18:53.842 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]

00:18:53.925 --> 00:18:56.886 position:50% align:center
She's still processing,
like all of us are.

00:18:56.970 --> 00:18:58.930 position:50% align:center
This is a lot.

00:18:59.014 --> 00:19:02.183 position:50% align:center
I mean, do we really
have to kill Yuito?

00:19:02.267 --> 00:19:04.686 position:50% align:center
Also, are we sure we want
to take Seiran's side

00:19:04.769 --> 00:19:06.229 position:50% align:center
after all this?

00:19:06.312 --> 00:19:07.564 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:19:07.647 --> 00:19:10.108 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI sobs]

00:19:10.191 --> 00:19:11.401 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Naomi?

00:19:18.074 --> 00:19:20.243 position:50% align:center
It's me.

00:19:20.326 --> 00:19:22.620 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI]
No one told me.

00:19:22.704 --> 00:19:27.000 position:50% align:center
I can't believe that's what
those awful drugs are made from.

00:19:27.083 --> 00:19:28.126 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]

00:19:28.209 --> 00:19:30.128 position:50% align:center
It sounds like she
found out the truth.

00:19:30.211 --> 00:19:34.174 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI sobs] Yes, I overheard
some of the lab personnel

00:19:34.257 --> 00:19:36.259 position:50% align:center
talking about it.

00:19:36.343 --> 00:19:40.638 position:50% align:center
They said Yuito and his
platoon saw it themselves!

00:19:40.722 --> 00:19:43.099 position:50% align:center
You didn't know, calm down!

00:19:43.183 --> 00:19:46.227 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI sobbing]
I can't live with that!

00:19:46.311 --> 00:19:48.855 position:50% align:center
Now that I know
it's human brains,

00:19:48.938 --> 00:19:52.901 position:50% align:center
I told them I don't
want any more of it!

00:19:52.984 --> 00:19:55.445 position:50% align:center
I don't need those drugs!

00:19:55.528 --> 00:19:56.780 position:50% align:center
[ALL grunt]

00:19:58.156 --> 00:20:02.410 position:50% align:center
[sobbing continues]

00:20:02.494 --> 00:20:03.912 position:50% align:center
Naomi...

00:20:03.995 --> 00:20:05.747 position:50% align:center
The truth is hard to bear.

00:20:05.830 --> 00:20:08.124 position:50% align:center
Then again, if it weren't for
the ampules, we wouldn't

00:20:08.208 --> 00:20:11.836 position:50% align:center
be able to have a conversation
with you, so it's not all bad.

00:20:11.920 --> 00:20:17.759 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI] Yes, that's true...
But consuming brains?

00:20:17.842 --> 00:20:22.555 position:50% align:center
If I do that, how am I any
different than those monsters?

00:20:22.639 --> 00:20:26.434 position:50% align:center
You're not a monster!
You're still my big sister!

00:20:28.520 --> 00:20:32.357 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI]
Thanks for that, Kasane, really.

00:20:32.440 --> 00:20:34.526 position:50% align:center
I hate to complain, it's just...

00:20:35.735 --> 00:20:40.365 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI] This is so hard for me!
I can't go on this way.

00:20:40.448 --> 00:20:43.159 position:50% align:center
If I have to do such a
horrible thing to survive,

00:20:43.243 --> 00:20:46.579 position:50% align:center
then I'd rather they
just let me die!

00:20:46.663 --> 00:20:48.206 position:50% align:center
Hang in there!

00:20:48.289 --> 00:20:51.334 position:50% align:center
We'll figure out a way to get
you back to your old self!

00:20:51.418 --> 00:20:55.672 position:50% align:center
I swear! So please,
don't give up yet!

00:20:56.715 --> 00:21:02.971 position:50% align:center
[NAOMI] Kasane. I'm sorry,
but I think I want to be alone.

00:21:03.054 --> 00:21:04.723 position:50% align:center
[KASANE whimpers]

00:21:08.977 --> 00:21:10.437 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Sis...

00:21:13.982 --> 00:21:16.151 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
I'm okay, don't worry.

00:21:17.485 --> 00:21:19.738 position:50% align:center
Remember not to
overdo it, though.

00:21:19.821 --> 00:21:21.406 position:50% align:center
You should be careful.

00:21:21.489 --> 00:21:24.909 position:50% align:center
Right. Thanks, you guys.

00:21:24.993 --> 00:21:28.038 position:50% align:center
Well, for now, let's just
wait for the Major General.

00:21:28.121 --> 00:21:30.749 position:50% align:center
Yeah, but why do you
think he called us here?

00:21:30.832 --> 00:21:33.084 position:50% align:center
I wonder if he's figured
out our next move.

00:21:34.502 --> 00:21:37.422 position:50% align:center
Did he know about
this from the start?

00:21:37.505 --> 00:21:39.007 position:50% align:center
Remember, he's a Spring.

00:21:39.090 --> 00:21:41.676 position:50% align:center
One of the Spring
Pharmaceuticals brood.

00:21:41.760 --> 00:21:45.472 position:50% align:center
That's a good point. Of course
he would know some secrets.

00:21:45.555 --> 00:21:46.848 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI, HANABI sigh]

00:21:50.435 --> 00:21:51.603 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Hm.

00:21:53.772 --> 00:21:56.941 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] About what you found.
Wataru told me.

00:21:57.025 --> 00:21:59.861 position:50% align:center
And since it doesn't expressly
affect our efforts,

00:21:59.944 --> 00:22:01.946 position:50% align:center
I informed the
proper authorities.

00:22:02.030 --> 00:22:04.783 position:50% align:center
Wait. Was that a good idea?

00:22:04.866 --> 00:22:08.036 position:50% align:center
That's your family's business,
so it'll cause problems for you,

00:22:08.119 --> 00:22:09.204 position:50% align:center
won't it?

00:22:09.287 --> 00:22:11.414 position:50% align:center
That was why I did it.

00:22:11.498 --> 00:22:13.458 position:50% align:center
What better way to
seem trustworthy to this

00:22:13.541 --> 00:22:16.878 position:50% align:center
corrupt government, than by
accusing my own flesh and blood?

00:22:16.961 --> 00:22:18.171 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:22:18.254 --> 00:22:21.132 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] Besides,
Seiran's research facility,

00:22:21.216 --> 00:22:23.301 position:50% align:center
that was my own suggestion.

00:22:23.385 --> 00:22:25.261 position:50% align:center
Mine and Karen's, that is.

00:22:25.345 --> 00:22:26.554 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:22:27.639 --> 00:22:32.644 position:50% align:center
♪